{
  "text": "The derivation of this identity is straightforward, and is given in [CITATION_1] . With this summary of definitions and numerical data we prepared the background for the main results of the present work, where we use the trace formula to express the spectral form factor in terms of the variance of the fluctuations in the counting of the number of t-periodic nb walks. By assuming that the spectral fluctuations for the graphs are given by RMT, we shall derive the variance-to-mean ratio of t-periodic nbwalks on graphs. This approach is similar in spirit to the work of Keating and Snaith [CITATION_2] who computed the mean moments of the Riemann \u03b6 function on the critical line, assuming that the fluctuations of the Riemann zeros follow the predictions of RMT for the Circular Unitary Ensemble (CUE).",
  "citation_candidates": [
